  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 10-25.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - THE REIGN OF JOASH. The writer passes from the reign of Jehoahaz, Jehu's son, to that of Joash, Jehu's grandson, which he seems to have intended at first to dispatch in the short space of four verses (vers. 10-13). He afterwards, however, saw reason to add to his narrative, first, an account of an interview between Joash and Elisha, shortly Before the death of the latter (vers. 14-19); secondly, an account of a miracle wrought soon afterwards by means of Elisha's corpse (vers. 20, 21); and thirdly, a brief notice of Joash's Syrian war (vers. 22-25). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 10.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "In the thirty and seventh year of Joash King of Judah.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Three years before his death, since he reigned forty years  (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 12:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The two Joashes were thus contemporary monarchs for the space of three years. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Began Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz to reign ever Israel in Samaria, and reigned sixteen years.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The construction is the same as that of ver. 1, and is equally ungrammatical. Our translators again amend the faulty phrase by introducing the words \"and reigned\" The \"sixteen years\" of the reign of Joash are confirmed by Josephus ('Ant. Jud.,' 9:8. § 6), but still present some difficulty (see the comment on 2 Kings 14:23). 2 Kings 13:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
